    "description": "We at Dr. Reddy's Laboratories International Enterprises are looking for an experienced Medical Officer based out of Bengaluru. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Dr. Reddy's Laboratories International Enterprises:\nDr. Reddy's Laboratories International Enterprises is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Dr. Reddy's Laboratories International Enterprises!",
